-- Mexico Organized-Crime Deaths Reach Almost 25,000 Since '06, Official Says
-- Jose Enrique Arrioja
-- 2010-07-16T15:43:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-16/mexico-organized-crime-deaths-reach-almost-25-000-since-06-official-says.html

          
          
             Mexico has reported 24,826 deaths
related to organized crime since President Felipe Calderon took
office in December 2006, Attorney General Arturo Chavez Chavez
said.  
 The country has had 7,048 such deaths so far this year,
Chavez said at an event in Mexico City.  
